text: Delbert Leroy "Del" Latta (March 5, 1920 - May 12, 2016) was an American politician. He served as member of the United States House of Representatives from 1959 through 1989. He was a Republican. He was born in Weston, Ohio. Latta died in Bowling Green, Ohio on May 12, 2016, aged 96. ==References== ==Other websites== * * Category:1920 births Category:2016 deaths Category:United States representatives from Ohio Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
